Equation (16) reveals that the bargaining power of shareholders η, liquidation costs α, the corporate tax rate τ, and costs of financial distress φ affect the value‐maximizing coupon payment. In particular, leverage should increase with corporate tax rate τ (the benefit of debt) and decrease with liquidation costs α and costs of financial distress φ (the costs of debt). In addition, the larger the bargaining power of shareholders, the greater the cost of debt and hence the lower optimal leverage. These effects are illustrated intable 1and infigure 2c
               , which report the firm’s leverage choices in different economic environments.
